text: Quofaloma is an unincorporated community in Holmes County, in the U.S. state of Mississippi. ==History== Quofaloma is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either "panther branch" or "quail cover". A variant name is "Quofaloma Plantation". ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Mississippi Category:Unincorporated communities in Holmes County, Mississippi
title: Quofaloma, Mississippi
